<Author>lozziep
<Content>Wouldn't suggest this to anyone I stayed here for two weeks for business.The service and food in the restaurant was way below standard for the prices, although I found the room service waiter very polite and attentive.Every morning a housekeeper barged into my room wanting to know if I had any cleaning, without waiting for me to open the door myself. The person who cleaned my room more often than not took all of my items from where I had left them for my convenience and left them in different places. One day they re-arranged the way I had hung my clothes in the closet! Things that were clearly not rubbish were thrown away.The walls in the room were paper thin, to the extent that one night I needed to telephone the guest next door and ask them to turn down their television so I could sleep. The beds were tiny, masquerading as doubles, but really only single beds. Also, mattresses about as comfortable as sleeping on the floor and no extra blankets provided.They advertise wireless internet, but it there is a cost involved, and it is very unreliable which is not what I expect from a business hotel. 
