<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Bristol's an old favourite I've been staying at the Bristol on and off for twenty years. I think it offers very good value considering its excellent location. One block from Reforma Avenue and the Zona Rosa, and one block from the US and British Embassies. The rooms are very large and clean and the bathrooms perfectly adequate. The staff are friendly and it has the air of a family hotel. The restaurant/coffee shop is adequate but no more than that. General clientele is Mexican attending conferences and I've never heard any rowdyness. The business centre is modest, but you can send e-mails and get on the web OK. There's no gym or swimming pool but then, what do you expect for US$60? 
